  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a neural-network surrogate model used to predict pump-induced hemolysis for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The surrogate replaces expensive CFD evaluations across the 5 flow-speed operating envelope. COU1 evaluates whether the ML model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A two-seed training comparison was performed and agreement was judged acceptable; no statistical characterisation of seed-to-seed variance is provided.",
